This was one of my last ideas for April Fools. I was kind of proud of it:


EDH NEWS ALERT: Owing to the “auto-include” status Sol Ring enjoys in the Commander format, Commander Deck restrictions have now been expanded to 101 unique cards, up from a previous 100. 

This is a startling change, but thankfully, our EDHREC reporters were on the scene to ask some important questions. 

“We on the Rules Committee have long been troubled by the prevalence of Sol Ring,” said Sheldon Menery in a last-minute interview. “We considered banning it outright, but unfortunately, that decision simply wasn’t controversial enough. We decided that we could free up the “Sol Ring slot” in everyone’s deck by just letting everyone play an additional card!”

Unfortunately, Sheldon was unavailable for further comment, as he hastily proceeded to his weekly ritualistic sacrifice of a copy of Kalemne, Disciple of Iroas, a practice he attests ‘appeases the one true god, Leovold, thus ensuring Boros will never achieve true Commander enlightenment.’ 

Player reactions have expectedly been mixed. Said one enthusiastic newcomer, “One of my favorite movies has always been 101 Dalmatians! Now I can make a deck called 101 Damnations!”

Others have accused the Rules Committee of being in the pockets of Wizards of the Coast, arguing that this was quote, “Just a way to make sure we have to buy more cards from WotC. They’re all corporate shills!”

In unrelated news, packs of Dragon Shield card sleeves are now rumored to no longer contain extra sleeves, but merely a flat 100, necessitating that players buy extra packs to fully sleeve their 101-card Commander decks.

text: He's down on Brawl having no commander damage, which I'm going to read between the lines and assume he'd then be even more down on losing it in actual commadner

On walkers as commanders: "I've been asked numerous times if Brawl allowing Planeswalkers will open the door to us reconsidering it. The first thing I'll say is that we try to never close doors. The second thing is that the presence of them as available commanders in Brawl probably makes us less likely to pull the trigger on making a change, since now there's an option for folks who want to try it out (beyond the normal option of convincing your playgroup to give it a whirl). I'm obviously quite curious about how it works out, although my current thought is that it can be good for Brawl and not good for Commander at the same time."
